    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point in Gunnar Henderson, whose 79.79 score makes him our most potent asset. Henderson benefits from a favorable matchup against Shane Smith (4.20 xERA) and, crucially, a slow-delivery variable that boosts his stolen base potential\u2014a vital metric given our strategy to prioritize speed. Josh Lowe (71.68) and Kyle Tucker (67.98) round out the high-ceiling core; Lowe is particularly well-positioned to capitalize on a soft matchup against Reynaldo L\u00f3pez (6.36 xERA), while Tucker\u2019s xwOBA stability makes him a lock despite the tough draw against Kevin Gausman.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved leaving Vladimir Guerrero Jr. on the bench (50.61). While his baseline production remains elite, the optimizer penalized him heavily for a daunting matchup against Yoshinobu Yamamoto (3.32 xERA) and negative platoon indicators, keeping him narrowly behind the utility slot occupancy of Marcell Ozuna, who earns his spot largely through elite BvP history (35 PA). Conversely, Luis Garc\u00eda Jr. remains in the starting lineup despite a 15% penalty from a dynamic platoon disadvantage against Matthew Liberatore, underscoring our commitment to daily efficiency over pure name value. \n\nRisk management remains critical as we navigate the \"Lineup Pending\" status across the board. Luis Robert Jr. (46.41) carries the highest risk profile today, as a combination of Zac Gallen\u2019s effective stuff and unfavorable wind conditions creates a \"Wind In\" penalty that drags his efficiency toward the floor. Owners should monitor the official lineup releases closely; any shift out of the top-of-order spots for our projected starters\u2014particularly for Baldwin or Nunez\u2014could necessitate a move to the bench to protect our game caps against sub-optimal scoring outputs.",
